Heavy rain Saturday morning disrupted voting at Unit 13, Agudama Polling Unit. It rained for almost an hour and ad-hoc staff had to move the station to a shade to give more tent room for voters. The few Security personnel, however, found it a struggle to control the crowd who had begun to grow impatient. To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .